modules.description: This module implements an HTTP client that establishes connections using a configurable TCP stack and Happy Eyeballs algorithm for address resolution. It provides a `connect` function that initiates an HTTP connection within a MirageOS context, returning a handle for issuing requests. It works with TCP connection modules and resolver implementations to support efficient, multi-address HTTP communication in MirageOS applications.

This module implements an HTTP client for MirageOS, handling connections over a Mirage-compatible network stack. It provides a `connect` function that establishes an HTTP client session using a given network context. Use it to send HTTP requests and receive responses in unikernel applications.

This module executes HTTP requests with support for HTTP/1.1 and HTTP/2, handling TLS configuration, redirects, and custom headers while processing responses incrementally through a streaming body function. It integrates with MirageOS network stacks via child modules that establish connections using TCP or network interfaces, supporting Happy Eyeballs for address resolution and unikernel-compatible communication. Main data types include connection handles and request/response structures, with operations like `connect`, `call`, and streaming body handlers. You can use it to securely fetch web resources, authenticate via TLS, and handle redirects automatically in MirageOS applications.
